The  policy  for  conducting  Audit  Committee  meetings  are outlined  in  the  Audit  Committee  Charter.  These  meetings convene a minimum of 4 (four) times annually or as required by  the  Board  of  Commissioners.  The  Audit  Committee  has the authority to invite relevant parties to participate in these meetings.  Additionally,  when  required,  the  Audit  Committee may  arrange  closed  meetings  with  the  Internal  Audit  Unit, Corporate Secretary, Group Legal, Risk Management Function, External Auditor, and other relevant parties within the Company.

In 2023, the Audit Committee conducted 6 (six) meetings with an attendance rate of 100%. The meeting agenda included topics, such  as  updates  on  past  performance  reviews,  manpower, safety, legal issues, and internal audit issues.

Throughout 2023, the duties of the Audit Committee related to the following matters:

- 1. Assessed  the  performance  of  the  external  auditor  for  the 2022 fiscal year;
- 2.  Formulated selection criteria and provided recommendations on the appointment of external auditors for the 2023 fiscal year to the Board of Commissioners, serving as a basis for consideration in proposing their appointment to the GMS;
- 3. Scrutinized the independency and objectivity of the designated  external  auditor,  KAP  Tanudiredja,  Wibisana, Rintis dan Rekan (a member of the PwC global network);
- 4.  Examined the scope of the external auditor's annual audit program;
- 5. Reviewed the results of the external auditor's examination of the Company's Financial Statements;
- 6. Evaluated the Company's Governance in relation to:
- a. Financial Statements  and  other  financial  information submitted to government institutions and the public;
- b.  Internal control process;
- c. The audit process;
- d.  Compliance with laws and regulations; and
- e. Risk management process;
- 7. Held annual meetings with external auditors;
- 8. Conducted 6 (six) meetings with the Company's accounting, finance, personnel, legal, internal control, and risk management officers; and
- 9. Submitted  and  presented  6  (six)  reports  to  the  Board  of Commissioners.

